<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I hate web applications. They are super slow, clunky, do not have good shortcuts. Do not integrate well with the command line. </p> <p>I have shifted to using many command line tools like pandoc, pdd, stopwatch, timer etc to avoid using many web applications. I don&#39;t use google docs, sheets or drive too and use the desktop programs like libre office, vim etc. </p> <p>But there are still many web applications which are hard to replace like </p> <ul> <li>Youtube<br/></li> <li>Google maps<br/></li> <li>Reddit<br/></li> <li>Gmail<br/></li> <li>Netflix<br/></li> <li>Amazon music<br/></li> <li>Whatsapp web </li> <li>Notion<br/></li> </ul> <p>Do you guys find any good alternatives to these?</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/LowCom"> /u/LowCom </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w164if/what_are_good_replacements_to_common_web/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/w164if/what_are_good_replacements_to_common_web/">[comments]</a></span>